Package sx.blah.discord.util

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Image
    Represents an avatar image.
    Opus
    This is taken from https://github.com/tbocek/opus-wrapper
    Slight modification to how it loads the native library.
    Credit for creation of this wrapper goes to the original developer: Thomas Bocek (tbocek)
    RequestBuffer.IRequest<T>
    This is used to model the request, NOTE: it IS a functional interface so you are encouraged to use lambdas!
    RequestBuffer.IVoidRequest
    This is used to model a request which returns nothing, NOTE: it IS a functional interface so you are encouraged to use lambdas!
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioChannel
    This is used to interface with voice channels.
    MessageBuilder
    Utility class designed to make message sending easier.
    MessageComparator
    This is a comparator built to compare messages based on their timestamps
    MessageList
    This class is a custom implementation of List for retrieving discord messages.
    MessageList.MessageListEventListener
    This is used to automatically update the message list.
    NativeUtils
    A simple library class which helps with loading dynamic libraries stored in the JAR archive.
    Opus.OpusCustomDecoder  
    Opus.OpusCustomEncoder  
    Opus.OpusCustomMode  
    Opus.OpusDecoder  
    Opus.OpusEncoder  
    Opus.OpusMSDecoder  
    Opus.OpusMSEncoder  
    Opus.OpusRepacketizer  
    RequestBuffer
    This is utility class intended to help with dealing with HTTP429Exceptions by queueing rate-limited operations until they can be sent.
    RequestBuffer.RequestFuture<T>
    This represents a future request which may or may not have been executed at the time of construction.
    ServiceUtil
    Internal class used to load the Java Service Provider Interfaces used by JDA.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MessageBuilder.Styles
    Enum describing Markdown formatting that can be used in chat.
    Requests
    Represents request types to be sent.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    HTTP429Exception
    Represents a 429 TOO MANY REQUESTS return code from a url connection.
